<div id="review_4018209020" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4018209020" />
    <a title="Stephanie Carr" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/81569130-stephanie-carr"><img alt="Stephanie Carr" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1553900728p2/81569130.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4018209020?book_show_action=true">May 28, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Stephanie Carr" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Stephanie Carr" href="/user/show/81569130-stephanie-carr">Stephanie Carr</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/81569130-stephanie-carr?shelf=sci-fi">sci-fi</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/81569130-stephanie-carr?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4018209020" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17130255551179080561">Sad to think this was McCaffrey&apos;s last Pern novel. It sets itself up for more adventures by the end. I do like F&apos;lessan very much as a character. It&apos;s been fun to see him grow up from that little one running around Benden Weyr with Jaxom.</span>
  <span id="freeText17130255551179080561" style="display:none">Sad to think this was McCaffrey's last Pern novel. It sets itself up for more adventures by the end. I do like F'lessan very much as a character. It's been fun to see him grow up from that little one running around Benden Weyr with Jaxom.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17130255551179080561" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

