<span id="freeTextContainer12682410797817651296">&quot;Ours not to ponder what were fair in life, but, finding what may be, make it fair up to our means.&quot;<br/><br/><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1543389533i/26658229._SY540_.jpg' width='400' height='400' alt='description' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/>This was the first Pern book I ever read, way back in Middle School, so suffice it to say, I understood literally nothing about what was going on. I bought it as an impulse cover-buy because of the cool dragon on the cover, but then (obviously) had to go back and start at the beginning to understand what was going on.<br/><br/>I like the love story here between a gold and a green rider, it&apos;s something very </span>
  <span id="freeText12682410797817651296" style="display:none">"Ours not to ponder what were fair in life, but, finding what may be, make it fair up to our means."<br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1543389533i/26658229._SY540_.jpg" width="400" height="400" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>This was the first Pern book I ever read, way back in Middle School, so suffice it to say, I understood literally nothing about what was going on. I bought it as an impulse cover-buy because of the cool dragon on the cover, but then (obviously) had to go back and start at the beginning to understand what was going on.<br><br>I like the love story here between a gold and a green rider, it's something very uncommon in the Pern world, so that was nice to see something different. But besides that, it reads a lot like the rest of the series, save that we're getting more and more technology unearthed and learning to use it, which is both cool and sad because it means the Pernese way of life will completely change.</span>
