        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2041394310" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4863458922052877450">With the Red Star no longer a threat, some people can&apos;t understand why Thread has not stopped falling immediately; others don&apos;t believe that this is the end of it — or don&apos;t want to. These hidebound dissidents are determined to &quot;return&quot; Pern to the way it was before the discover of AIVAS, and the technology it has provided.<br/><br/>Meanwhile, the dragonriders are seeking a solution of their own: what will they do when this Pass ends, and they are no longer supported by the tithes of Hold and Hall? Bronze</span>
  <span id="freeText4863458922052877450" style="display:none">With the Red Star no longer a threat, some people can't understand why Thread has not stopped falling immediately; others don't believe that this is the end of it — or don't want to. These hidebound dissidents are determined to "return" Pern to the way it was before the discover of AIVAS, and the technology it has provided.<br /><br />Meanwhile, the dragonriders are seeking a solution of their own: what will they do when this Pass ends, and they are no longer supported by the tithes of Hold and Hall? Bronze rider F'lessan, son of F'lar and Lessa, along with young green rider Tai, almost accidentally discover an answer.<br /><br />Once again, McCaffrey does not disappoint — her world is fully-formed and believable, as are the characters, whose behavior is understandable. Highly recommended — but read the earlier books first! </span>
